Hmm... I didn't find any case when the function `parse` returns any type except a type `Object`:

```
> querystring.parse('a=1')
{ a: '1' }
> querystring.parse('a=')
{ a: '' }
> querystring.parse('=1')
{ '': '1' }
> querystring.parse('')
{}
> querystring.parse(1)
{}
```

even if it used with a custom `decodeURIComponent`:

```
> querystring.parse('a=1', null, null, {decodeURIComponent: x => true})
{ true: true }
> querystring.parse('a=1', null, null, {decodeURIComponent: () => {}})
{ undefined: undefined }

```

Are you sure about it?

